title: For Sale:  Witness P-S 9mm
location: NW San Antonio, San Antonio, Texas
postcontent:
The Witness P-S may be one of the best kept shooting secrets these days.
It’s not the Pavona or the Compact.
It’s full size, but it has a thin grip.  Even people that don’t have huge hand can comfortably grip and shoot this gun.  Even with the smallish grip, it still holds 16 + 1.
The P is for polymer and the S is for either great ergonomic small frame or standard frame, which is smaller than the huge grips that many folks have a hard time shooting.
The slide riding inside the frame, like a CZ 75, cuts down on recoil and makes it easier to shoot and control.
Black slide, but the frame is pretty neat dark blue color.  The Blue is very difficult to find. 
24 oz with no magazine and 32 oz with a fully loaded magazine and one in the pipe
Tanfoglio makes it in Italy, but EAA imports it.
Can be converted to a .22lr or 40 cal.

title: For Sale/Trade:  HK P30 V1 LEM 9mm for AR10/AR15 or P30sk
postcontent:
I have a 2014 HK P30 V1 LEM in 9mm. I have had it since Fall 2015. 

For those that do not know, the LEM trigger is one smooth, long, ~4lb pull. Many people who have the P30 type guns modify the triggers to LEM, which HK does not authorize/acknowledge. This is a factory LEM gun. 

Gun is in 90-95% condition. Local stores would charge you $1000 for it. A great price for a gun that is a few months old. A few years ago this model went 90k+ rounds, with cleanings every 6000 rounds or so in harsh conditions. 

So why am I selling/trading such an awesome gun? I could use the money elsewhere. Specifically, something more concealable to potentially compliment my open carry full-size gun, and well I have taken a liking to HK so I'd like to have at least one - hence I am looking for the SK version (cheaper). Why not a VP9? I don't like striker fired guns.  

Or I'll take a reliable AR15 or AR10, as I don't have a rifle. 

Send me an offer.
